ce between these thinkers and envisions a "local" emancipatory project that, noting the specifics of the Iranian case, takes lessons from the Western experience without blind imitation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical culturezIran. 0aPolitical sciencezIranxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical sciencezIran. 0aReligion and politicszIran. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Politics. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Critique. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion and Politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847380240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438473802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438473802/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles